<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="DiffQuotient" checkit-title="Difference Quotient">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Suppose that there is a function <m>g</m> such that <m>g(-1) = 1.4</m> and <m>g(-0.9) = 0.8</m>. Use these values to estimate <m>g'(-1)</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>
            g'(-1) \approx \frac{ g(-0.9) - g(-1) }{ (-0.9) - (-1) } = 
            \frac{ (0.8) - (1.4) }{ (-0.9) - (-1) } = -6.00
        </me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
